						<div class="postbody">SDL 1 and SDL 2 are pretty different in this regard, so I would not be surprised if SDL 1 didn't offer or do the same thing.  One would really have to look at the SDL source to know.<br /><br />Okay, so there's a Python program that does some magic.  Great -- now either I have to find someone who can compile me an .exe of that Python program (yes it's possible to do this, trust me), or I have to install Python for Windows and risk making a mess of my system.  I have a friend who compiles Python stuff like this (his workplace demands compiled Python apps on Windows because, and I quote, &quot;installing Python on Windows is painful and makes a mess&quot;), so I'll ask him if maybe he can do that.</div>

